<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="114" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="114">
Two specimens were identified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
as types in the list of specimens examined. This included a staminate specimen (Vaupel 356 noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
as accessioned at HBG) and a pistillate specimen (K. and L. Rechinger n. 4334 noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
as accessioned at W). The pistillate specimen of Rechinger is not extant at W (pers. comm. A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löckher">Loeckher</normalizedToken>
, Department of Botany at Naturhistorisches Museum Wien). Efforts are underway to locate type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Skottsb." baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia samoense" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="samoense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Astelia samoense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
held in herbaria globally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="114">
Diacritical signs, which should be suppressed in species names (
<bibRefCitation author="International Botanical Congress and JH Wiersema" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, Germany" pageId="12" pageNumber="117" refId="B14" refString="International Botanical Congress and JH Wiersema, 2015. International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi and plants (Melbourne Code); adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress, Melbourne, Australia, July 2011. Appendices II-VIII. Regnum Vegetabile 157: Appendix 3, 163. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, Germany" title="International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi and plants (Melbourne Code); adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress, Melbourne, Australia, July 2011. Appendices II-VIII. Regnum Vegetabile 157: Appendix 3, 163" year="2015">International Botanical Congress and JH Wiersema 2015</bibRefCitation>
; Article 60.6) have not been transferred from 
<taxonomicName authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Birch" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum samoënse" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="samoënse">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">
Collospermum 
<normalizedToken originalValue="samoënse">samoense</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
